# Nested Objects

```jsx
const employees = [

    {
        id: 1,
        name: "John",
        address: {
            city: "Hyderabad"
        }
    },

    {
        id: 2,
        name: "Alice",
        address: {
            city: "Bangalore"
        }
    }

];
```

```jsx
employees.map((employee) => (

    <div key={employee.id}>

        <h2>{employee.name}</h2>

        <p>{employee.address.city}</p>

    </div>

))
```

Output

```
John
Hyderabad

Alice
Bangalore
```

