# Quick Revision

| Concept | Example |
|---------|----------|
| Array | `["Apple", "Mango"]` |
| Traverse | `array.map()` |
| Current Item | `(fruit)` |
| Index | `(fruit, index)` |
| Object | `student.name` |
| Nested Object | `employee.address.city` |
| Unique Key | `key={student.id}` |

---

# Interview Answer

> **In React, the `map()` method is used to traverse arrays and render multiple JSX elements dynamically. Each element generated by `map()` should have a unique `key` prop so that React can efficiently identify and update items during rendering.**
